  "texts": [
    "As scholars of technology and ethics, we are interested in the intersection of rhetoric and digital technology, specifically pertaining to AI and LLMs.",
    "For this, a subset of empirical digital rhetoric, in particular, proves to be a fruitful methodology for analysis.",
    "Digital RhetoricWe here define digital rhetoric, following Samuel Mateus, as rhetoric \"concerned with the study of persuasion in digital environments including computers, video games, websites, and discourse on new media\" [43, p. 12].",
    "Empirical digital rhetoric \"measures and classifies the persuasive processes involved in computational systems\" [43, p. 12].",
    "That is to say, instead of examining how users apply rhetoric in online communities or \"collective discourses\" [43, p. 12], it is concerned with how computational systems themselves produce persuasion."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}